		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://arstechnica.com/?p=1196745</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Vega 56 should have led to lower prices. Instead, the 1070 Ti maintains the status quo.]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="rss-wrap">
<figure class="intro-image intro-left"><img src="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/DSC09934-800x534.jpg"><p class="caption" style="font-size:0.8em"><a href="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/DSC09934.jpg" class="enlarge-link" data-height="1670" data-width="2500">Enlarge</a> (credit: Mark Walton)</p>  </figure><div><a name="page-1"></a></div>
<table class="specifications right" width="300"><tbody>
